<node id="&quot;LEFT VENTRICLE (LV)&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Left Ventricle (LV) is part of the heart responsible for pumping oxygenated blood into the aorta and throughout the body. Its cavity size and systolic function are normal, with an ejection fraction of 50-55%."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-8cedf57d6622effa5339b81b3ef19b5d</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;RIGHT VENTRICLE (RV)&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Right Ventricle (RV) is part of the heart responsible for pumping deoxygenated blood to the lungs. Its cavity size and free wall motion are normal, with no significant changes noted."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-8cedf57d6622effa5339b81b3ef19b5d</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;AORTA&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"The Aorta is the largest artery in the body, carrying oxygenated blood from the left ventricle of the heart to the rest of the body. It has a normal sinus diameter and ascending/descending diameters with no dissection or significant atheroma noted."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-8cedf57d6622effa5339b81b3ef19b5d</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;AORTIC VALVE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"The Aortic Valve is responsible for ensuring that blood flows only from the left ventricle to the aorta. It is mildly thickened but mobile, with no stenosis or regurgitation noted."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-8cedf57d6622effa5339b81b3ef19b5d</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;MITRAL VALVE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"The Mitral Valve separates the left atrium and left ventricle of the heart. It is mildly thickened with mild annular calcification and mild-moderate central regurgitation."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-8cedf57d6622effa5339b81b3ef19b5d</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;TRICUSPID VALVE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"The Tricuspid Valve separates the right atrium and right ventricle of the heart. It has normal leaflets but shows trace regurgitation."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-8cedf57d6622effa5339b81b3ef19b5d</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;PERICARDIUM&quot;">
